{"word":"ἀποδεκτέος","slug":"ἀποδεκτέος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀποδεκτέος</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:verbal Adjective'>verb. <a href='S:Adjective'>adj.</a></a> of <el>ἀποδέχομαι.</el>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>one must receive from others</i>, <el>τι</el> <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>one must accept, allow, admit</i>, <el>τι</el> <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>; <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a> et <a href='S:participle'>part.</a>, <el>ἀπ. τινὸς λέγοντος</el> <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}